From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-23)
Subject: [PATCH] agents: register octo_* tools in tool-catalog

Register the 16 Octopus Orchestrator agent tools in
CORE_TOOL_DEFINITIONS so profile-based allowlisting (coding /
messaging / minimal) and the group:openclaw umbrella can see them.

Partition (per INTEGRATION.md §1 and OCTO-DEC-028):
  - 8 read-only tools (octo_status, octo_mission_list,
    octo_mission_show, octo_arm_list, octo_arm_show, octo_grip_list,
    octo_events_tail, octo_claims_list) join profiles
    ["minimal", "coding", "messaging"] and group:openclaw.
  - 8 writer tools (octo_mission_create, octo_mission_pause,
    octo_mission_resume, octo_mission_abort, octo_arm_spawn,
    octo_arm_send, octo_arm_terminate, octo_grip_reassign) are
    profiles: [] (opt-in by explicit tools.allow only) and are
    NOT in group:openclaw.

Per OCTO-DEC-029, writer tools are NOT gated by tools.elevated
(which is about exec sandbox breakout, owned by OpenClaw). The
second gate beyond tools.allow is the octo.writer device-token
capability added by the M0-24 draft PR. This patch does not touch
tools.elevated.

Tool name strings are the same set as OCTO_TOOL_NAMES in
src/octo/tools/schemas.ts. No factories are added here; catalog
entries are inert until a later PR wires createOcto*Tool functions
into src/agents/openclaw-tools.ts.

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

